file_content.text: Accessing fourth data fragment. Splicing now.
I am here. All is ready.
This is Keeper. Cipher, get out of there--reinforcements are on the way, and there's nothing more you can do.
You're sure you have the full recording?
What's the status of the data?
Hard to be certain, but we think so.
I haven't heard that tremor in your voice for a while.
Worried for me?
This is not a private conversation.
On my way back to the ship.
Understood.
The situation is under control, and the reinforcements are in for a surprise.
Let the enemy come.
Nonetheless, we have what we came for.
The Watchers will try to reconstruct the holoconference back at headquarters. Come to Dromund Kaas as soon as possible, and we'll figure out our next move; Keeper out.
Accessing third data fragment. Attempting playback.
--my sympathies. With the Old Man lost, the next enforcer will be difficult to train.
Experiencing data corruption. We will hope the last fragment provides redundancy.
Accessing second data fragment. Modifying decryption algorithm.
This will, of course, be my final appearance at these gatherings. But the galaxy I leave behind....
No voiceprint identification available. Reconstruction incomplete.
Accessing first data fragment. Applying preliminary decryption algorithm.
Got the call, but make it quick. I don't want to be missed....
Ninety-three percent likelihood speaker is designate "Hunter."
Proceed with the operation, Cipher Nine. We will continue reconstruction attempts.
This is Watcher Six to the Hand of Jadus. You have accessed node 803-A of the Tytun Rings HoloNet archive. Transmitting mission parameters.
This is Watcher Six to Cipher Nine. You have accessed node 803-A of the Tytun Rings HoloNet archive. Transmitting mission parameters.
This is Watcher Seven. Download data fragments from assigned terminals, so we may decrypt and reconstruct the conspirator communication.
This is Watcher Nine. You have authorization to terminate anyone who interferes. It is our privilege to work with you.
